  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for creating or cloning a typeface with variation and palette settings.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct` that bundles all the arguments needed to create or clone a
typeface with specific variation settings and palette configuration. Pass it to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments@)> to produce a customized
typeface instance.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap and must be used
within the same stack frame where the spans it holds are valid.

## Examples

```csharp
var coords = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
{
    new() { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
};
var overrides = new SKFontPaletteOverride[]
{
    new() { Index = 0, Color = 0xFFFF0000 },  // override first color with red
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex  = 0,
    PaletteIndex     = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = coords,
    PaletteOverrides = overrides,
};
using var clone = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
